cing.\", \"from\": 5397, \"to\": 5585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5397, \"end\": 5404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his credit\", \"from\": 5409, \"to\": 5419}, {\"ngram\": \"resistance\", \"from\": 5430, \"to\": 5440}, {\"ngram\": \"his own pace\", \"from\": 5497, \"to\": 5509}, {\"ngram\": \"an attempt\", \"from\": 5518, \"to\": 5528}, {\"ngram\": \"the chase\", \"from\": 5541, \"to\": 5550}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal placing\", \"from\": 5569, \"to\": 5584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"3.8km:Heading through the Louvre and toward the finish along the Seine, Evenepoel suffers an extremely ill-timed flat time, which sets off a panicked bike change.\", \"from\": 5589, \"to\": 5751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5615, \"end\": 5621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.999999972249498, \"rank\": 2.7750126925231582e-08, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}, {\"begin\": 5654, \"end\": 5659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4231031325741708e-26, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the finish\", \"from\": 5633, \"to\": 5643}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 5661, \"to\": 5670}, {\"ngram\": \"an extremely ill-timed flat time\", \"from\": 5679, \"to\": 5711}, {\"ngram\": \"a panicked bike change\", \"from\": 5728, \"to\": 5750}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While he has 1'31 on the peloton and 1'15 on Madouas (who is still fighting to hold off the chase), Evenepoel has no way of knowing his lead is relatively safe due to the lack of race radios.\", \"from\": 5752, \"to\": 5943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5797, \"end\": 5804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the peloton\", \"from\": 5773, \"to\": 5784}, {\"ngram\": \"the chase\", \"from\": 5840, \"to\": 5849}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 5852, \"to\": 5861}, {\"ngram\": \"no way\", \"from\": 5866, \"to\": 5872}, {\"ngram\": \"his lead\", \"from\": 5884, \"to\": 5892}, {\"ngram\": \"the lack\", \"from\": 5919, \"to\": 5927}, {\"ngram\": \"race radios\", \"from\": 5931, \"to\": 5942}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finish:After getting back up to speed, Evenepoel crosses the finish line, set spectacularly in front of the Eiffel Tower, and, in true showman fashion, poses for a clearly pre-planned photo-op to celebrate his historic TT/RR double gold performance.\", \"from\": 5947, \"to\": 6196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6166, \"end\": 6168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"score\": 0.9999999999845386, \"rank\": 1.5657918658629707e-11, \"text\": \"TT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Finish\", \"from\": 5947, \"to\": 5953}, {\"ngram\": \"speed\", \"from\": 5979, \"to\": 5984}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 5986, \"to\": 5995}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 6004, \"to\": 6019}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 6042, \"to\": 6047}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 6051, \"to\": 6067}, {\"ngram\": \"true showman fashion\", \"from\": 6077, \"to\": 6097}, {\"ngram\": \"a clearly pre-planned photo-op\", \"from\": 6109, \"to\": 6139}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chase Group Finish:Just over a minute behind, Madouas polishes off an incredible ride to hold on for silver, while his French teammate, Christophe Laporte, who has marked Matteo Jorgenson's attempts to bridge across through the final few laps, wins the sprint for third.\", \"from\": 6200, \"to\": 6470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6246, \"end\": 6253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 6319, \"end\": 6325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6300102675393169, \"rank\": 0.5743133257853111, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 6336, \"end\": 6354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christophe Laporte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\"}, {\"begin\": 6371, \"end\": 6387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matteo Jorgenson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an incredible ride\", \"from\": 6267, \"to\": 6285}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 6301, \"to\": 6307}, {\"ngram\": \"the final few laps\", \"from\": 6424, \"to\": 6442}, {\"ngram\": \"the sprint\", \"from\": 6449, \"to\": 6459}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To highlight the chaos of the race, Laporte, who finished third, did not realize he had finished on the podium, while fourth place, Attila Valter, celebrated thinking he had finished third.\", \"from\": 6471, \"to\": 6660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6603, \"end\": 6616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila_Valter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Attila Valter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila_Valter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila_Valter\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the chaos\", \"from\": 6484, \"to\": 6493}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 6497, \"to\": 6505}, {\"ngram\": \"Laporte\", \"from\": 6507, \"to\": 6514}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 6571, \"to\": 6581}, {\"ngram\": \"fourth place\", \"from\": 6589, \"to\": 6601}]}, {\"sentence\": \"1) The Unusually Small Field Perfectly Suited Remco Evenepoel's Attacking Style:The 24-year-old Belgian became the first male rider to complete the Olympic time trial and road race double with a trademark solo victory where instead of using layers of tactics and deception, he simply rode everyone off his wheel until he crossed the finish line for a major solo victory.\", \"from\": 6664, \"to\": 7034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6760, \"end\": 6767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999704969018, \"rank\": 2.9503064565917505e-08, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"1) The Unusually Small Field Perfectly Suited Remco Evenepoel's Attacking Style\", \"from\": 6664, \"to\": 6743}, {\"ngram\": \"the first male rider\", \"from\": 6775, \"to\": 6795}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic time trial and road race\", \"from\": 6808, \"to\": 6844}, {\"ngram\": \"a trademark solo victory\", \"from\": 6857, \"to\": 6881}, {\"ngram\": \"layers\", \"from\": 6905, \"to\": 6911}, {\"ngram\": \"tactics\", \"from\": 6915, \"to\": 6922}, {\"ngram\": \"deception\", \"from\": 6927, \"to\": 6936}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 6953, \"to\": 6961}, {\"ngram\": \"his wheel\", \"from\": 6966, \"to\": 6975}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 6993, \"to\": 7008}, {\"ngram\": \"a major solo victory\", \"from\": 7013, \"to\": 7033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2) Mathieu van der Poel's Aggressive Tactics Played Right Into Belgium's Hands:After coming into the race as a near-absurd pre-race favorite, the World Champion quickly put his team to work on the front before launching an attack once the race hit the Butte Montmartre, the hardest part of the Parisian circuit.\", \"from\": 7036, \"to\": 7347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7182, \"end\": 7196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\", \"score\": 0.9400405245317768, \"rank\": 0.06366367713924581, \"text\": \"World Champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"2) Mathieu van der Poel's Aggressive Tactics\", \"from\": 7036, \"to\": 7080}, {\"ngram\": \"Right\", \"from\": 7088, \"to\": 7093}, {\"ngram\": \"Belgium's Hands\", \"from\": 7099, \"to\": 7114}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 7133, \"to\": 7141}, {\"ngram\": \"a near-absurd pre-race favorite\", \"from\": 7145, \"to\": 7176}, {\"ngram\": \"his team\", \"from\": 7209, \"to\": 7217}, {\"ngram\": \"the front\", \"from\": 7229, \"to\": 7238}, {\"ngram\": \"an attack\", \"from\": 7256, \"to\": 7265}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 7271, \"to\": 7279}, {\"ngram\": \"the Butte Montmartre\", \"from\": 7284, \"to\": 7304}, {\"ngram\": \"the hardest part\", \"from\": 7306, \"to\": 7322}, {\"ngram\": \"the Parisian circuit\", \"from\": 7326, \"to\": 7346}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, he was duly marked by his lifelong rival, Wout van Aert, and, with other top favorites like Denmark's Mads Pedersen having no intention of letting a dual-superstar move ride clear, the duo quickly had company.\", \"from\": 7348, \"to\": 7572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7405, \"end\": 7418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wout van Aert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\"}, {\"begin\": 7455, \"end\": 7462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"score\": 0.9974182975841969, \"rank\": 0.0025883848524892268, \"text\": \"Denmark\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\"}, {\"begin\": 7465, \"end\": 7478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mads_Pedersen_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9973584045699821, \"rank\": 0.0026481297583575304, \"text\": \"Mads Pedersen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mads_Pedersen_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mads_Pedersen_(cyclist)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his lifelong rival\", \"from\": 7385, \"to\": 7403}, {\"ngram\": \"other top favorites\", \"from\": 7430, \"to\": 7449}, {\"ngram\": \"no intention\", \"from\": 7486, \"to\": 7498}, {\"ngram\": \"a dual-superstar move ride\", \"from\": 7510, \"to\": 7536}, {\"ngram\": \"the duo\", \"from\": 7544, \"to\": 7551}, {\"ngram\": \"company\", \"from\": 7564, \"to\": 7571}]}, {\"sentence\": \"3) The Hometown French Squad's Ultra-Pragmatic Racing Paid Off Perfectly:While the Dutch, Danish, and Belgian teams burned precious resources early in the race, controlling the gap to the early breakaway, the French, even with a strong four-rider team (the maximum allowable number), sat back and allowed their competitors to chase before unleashing a classic 'punt and squeeze' tactic that saw them sweep up the only two realistic podium spots.\", \"from\": 7574, \"to\": 8019, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7581, \"end\": 7589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancestral_home_(Chinese)\", \"score\": 0.5861652865887818, \"rank\": 0.34580216126350805, \"text\": \"Hometown\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancestral_home_(Chinese)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancestral_home_(Chinese)\"}, {\"begin\": 7590, \"end\": 7602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999946816301871, \"rank\": 5.318397664570617e-06, \"text\": \"French Squad\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 7657, \"end\": 7662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999943073269749, \"rank\": 2.7856647249293487e-06, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 7664, \"end\": 7670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"score\": 0.9999999963374648, \"rank\": 2.3083604443559893e-09, \"text\": \"Danish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\"}, {\"begin\": 7676, \"end\": 7683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999704969018, \"rank\": 2.9503064565917505e-08, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"precious resources\", \"from\": 7697, \"to\": 7715}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 7725, \"to\": 7733}, {\"ngram\": \"the gap\", \"from\": 7747, \"to\": 7754}, {\"ngram\": \"the early breakaway\", \"from\": 7758, \"to\": 7777}, {\"ngram\": \"a strong four-rider team\", \"from\": 7801, \"to\": 7825}, {\"ngram\": \"the maximum allowable number\", \"from\": 7827, \"to\": 7855}, {\"ngram\": \"their competitors\", \"from\": 7879, \"to\": 7896}, {\"ngram\": \"a classic 'punt and squeeze' tactic\", \"from\": 7924, \"to\": 7959}, {\"ngram\": \"the only two realistic podium spots\", \"from\": 7983, \"to\": 8018}]}, {\"sentence\": \"4) Behind the National Team Lineups, Two Trade Teams Had Big Days:One of the most interesting quirks of International racing (Olympics, Worlds & Continental Championships) is that riders who are paid incredibly well to work for one another 364 days of the year are suddenly thrust into the roles of rivals while riders who are fierce rivals (e.g., Van Aert & Evenepoel), are placed in the roles of teammates.\", \"from\": 8021, \"to\": 8429, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the National Team Lineups\", \"from\": 8031, \"to\": 8056}, {\"ngram\": \"Two Trade Teams\", \"from\": 8058, \"to\": 8073}, {\"ngram\": \"Big Days\", \"from\": 8078, \"to\": 8086}, {\"ngram\": \"the most interesting quirks\", \"from\": 8094, \"to\": 8121}, {\"ngram\": \"International racing\", \"from\": 8125, \"to\": 8145}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics\", \"from\": 8147, \"to\": 8155}, {\"ngram\": \"Worlds\", \"from\": 8157, \"to\": 8163}, {\"ngram\": \"Continental Championships\", \"from\": 8166, \"to\": 8191}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 8201, \"to\": 8207}, {\"ngram\": \"one another 364 days\", \"from\": 8249, \"to\": 8269}, {\"ngram\": \"the year\", \"from\": 8273, \"to\": 8281}, {\"ngram\": \"the roles\", \"from\": 8307, \"to\": 8316}, {\"ngram\": \"rivals\", \"from\": 8320, \"to\": 8326}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 8333, \"to\": 8339}, {\"ngram\": \"fierce rivals\", \"from\": 8348, \"to\": 8361}, {\"ngram\": \"e.g., Van Aert\", \"from\": 8363, \"to\": 8377}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 8380, \"to\": 8389}, {\"ngram\": \"the roles\", \"from\": 8406, \"to\": 8415}, {\"ngram\": \"teammates\", \"from\": 8419, \"to\": 8428}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Saturday's Road Race did not produce as many of the usual 'secret teammate' shenanigans that we have seen in the past (where trade teammates work for one another despite being on different national teams), it is interesting to look at how many riders each trade team placed in the top ten.\", \"from\": 8430, \"to\": 8725, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Saturday's Road Race\", \"from\": 8436, \"to\": 8456}, {\"ngram\": \"the usual 'secret teammate' shenanigans\", \"from\": 8484, \"to\": 8523}, {\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 8545, \"to\": 8553}, {\"ngram\": \"trade teammates\", \"from\": 8561, \"to\": 8576}, {\"ngram\": \"different national teams\", \"from\": 8615, \"to\": 8639}, {\"ngram\": \"how many riders\", \"from\": 8671, \"to\": 8686}, {\"ngram\": \"each trade team\", \"from\": 8687, \"to\": 8702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"5)International Courses Are Always More Difficult In Practice Than They Appear on Paper:While it would have been easy to look at the course and envision a Milano-Sanremo-type outcome, without the benefit of massive teams deep with firepower, the small pelotons inevitably break up due to constant attacks before the finish line.\", \"from\": 8729, \"to\": 9057, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"5)International Courses\", \"from\": 8729, \"to\": 8752}, {\"ngram\": \"Practice\", \"from\": 8782, \"to\": 8790}, {\"ngram\": \"Paper\", \"from\": 8811, \"to\": 8816}, {\"ngram\": \"the course\", \"from\": 8858, \"to\": 8868}, {\"ngram\": \"a Milano-Sanremo-type outcome\", \"from\": 8882, \"to\": 8911}, {\"ngram\": \"the benefit\", \"from\": 8921, \"to\": 8932}, {\"ngram\": \"massive teams\", \"from\": 8936, \"to\": 8949}, {\"ngram\": \"firepower\", \"from\": 8960, \"to\": 8969}, {\"ngram\": \"the small pelotons\", \"from\": 8971, \"to\": 8989}, {\"ngram\": \"constant attacks\"